description:
### Project overview

The current challenge  API works and solves a lot of problems we had with syncing data between Informix, Postgres,
Dynamo, and ElasticSearch, but at the cost of code and architectural complexity and the syncing isn't exactly right all the time. 
Also it is difficult to run locally as there are a number of dependencies, and running it also involves
potentially having to have VPN access to a Topcoder AWS account, which isn't possible if we ever wanted to work on it
with members.

So, we are aiming to revise the challenge API to reduce the complexity on the dependencies.
We need to **remove dependencies on Informix, Dynamo, and ElasticSearch** and **use Postgres with Prisma ORM** as the sole backend database.
After getting the Prisma schema created, we should remove the DAL / gRPC dependencies completely and update the existing code to just use prisma instead of saving/retrieving from ES/OS.

In order to achieve the above goal, we have updated the code in challenge [Topcoder Challenge  API: Update Code for Prisma Schema and updated Swagger](https://www.topcoder.com/challenges/7dc44b10-2e27-4e57-bec1-4891c34aec4a) and have written Data migration tools in challenge [Topcoder Challenge API: Data Migration Tool to Postgres](https://www.topcoder.com/challenges/22477223-2354-449d-a3b5-2d4d63c4cb25)

The goal for this challenge is to Add **ChallengePhase** Endpoints.

### Individual Requirements

Managing phases is an important part of the admin process, to correct issues, extend, open phases that were skipped by autopilot, etc...
In anticipation of having new features in the system-admin app for phase management, We need some new endpoints added to the challenge API. 
We need to add the following endpoints which operates on **ChallengePhase** model:
1. `GET /v6/challenges/{challengeId}/phases` 
  * Returns all phase information for that challenge **including the associated phase model and constraints model** .
2.  `GET /v6/challenges/{challengeId}/phases/{id}`, where id is the id value of the phase
  * Returns the information for a single phase associated with the challenge **including the associated phase model and constraints model** ;
  * Throw NotFoundError if challengeId or id does not have a corresponding record;
  * Throw NotFoundError if (challengeId, id) combination does not have a corresponding ChallengePhase record;
3.  `PATCH /v6/challenges/{challengeId}/phases/{id}`, where id is the id value of the phase
  * Partially update a phase.  For instance, if I only want to open the phase, I could give body: {"isOpen":true}  ;
  * Any combination of phase object values should be accepted;
  * Should return the updated ChallengePhase information;
  * Throw NotFoundError if challengeId or id does not have a corresponding record;
  * Throw NotFoundError if (challengeId, id) combination does not have a corresponding ChallengePhase record;
  * Validation rules are as follows when passing specified values:
		* challengeId should NOT be allowed to update;
		* name can not be null/empy;
		* isOpen should be false if it's passed as null;
		* phaseId should be a valid phase;
		* predecessor should point to a valid phase by looking in the Phase model of the same challenge;
		* duration should be greater than 0;
			* scheduledStartDate should not be after scheduledEndDate  if both provided; If only scheduledStartDate provided, should compare it with exist scheduledEndDate from database; also for scheduledEndDate;
		* actualStartDate should not be after actualEndDate if both provided; If only actualStartDate provided, should compare it with exist actualEndDate from database; also for actualEndDate;
		* For constraints array, if id is passed, we should check specified ChallengePhaseConstraint exists and it's for the ChallengePhase, and update it; if no id provided, we should insert one record into ChallengePhaseConstraint. And name and value are both required.
4. `DELETE /v6/challenges/{challengeId}/phases/{id}`, where id is the id value of the phase
  * Deletes a phase and recalculates the predecessors based on the predecessor associated with the same challenge.  This will mainly be used to delete any added phases that aren't needed.  For instance, if we want to rewind a challenge and remove the Post-Mortem phase and reopen submission, which is something we need to do recently. ;
  * Throw NotFoundError if challengeId or id does not have a corresponding record;
  * Throw NotFoundError if (challengeId, id) combination does not have a corresponding ChallengePhase record;
  * 
5. Refactor the **ChallengePhaseController** to **PhaseController** as it's actually for Phase model. Also do the same refactor for the related tests, etc. And write a brand new **ChallengePhaseController** and related service for the new endpoints.
6. Write postman collections for the new endpoints.

### Code

- Challenge API code repo: https://github.com/topcoder-platform/challenge-api-v6/tree/develop

### Unit tests

Unit tests are in scope for this challenge, but any existing tests are expected to pass as they do now - we can't break any tests that are currently passing.

### Code quality
Please make sure you're following the code base quality & standards. Do not refactor/modify or start a new code styling. 

### Submission

Your submission should include:

* A patch file against the develop branch of Challenge API, hash cba01ac361ddd020b0c005d75e5bb54516565386 or later
* A comprehensive README that covers the deployment and configuration of the code (if any configuration changes were required)
* A validation markdown file that covers how you tested the new project functionality
